Hello, my friend. I created this channel as a soft place for those walking the long road of healing. For the ones who cry while washing dishes, who feel the weight of life even during the simplest moments. For the ones who keep going even when their hearts feel tired.

You are not alone here.
You are worthy of love, of safety, of being seen and honored in this life.

These videos are meant to strengthen the parts of you that have been overlooked, silenced, or worn down. I hope they help you reconnect with the person you were always meant to be — your noble, whole, restored self.

May this be a place where you return home to yourself.
Where you remember who you were before the trauma.
Where you rediscover your true north.

And always, from my heart to yours:
Don’t give up on yourself — I won’t allow you to do that.

Ich bin ein Hobbykomponist und habe mir alles selber beigebracht und bin 19. Ich schreibe klassische Musik und experimentiere sehr gerne mit ihr. Ich schreibe alles mögliche was mir gerade einfällt und wozu ich gerade Lust habe. Ich achte nicht unbedingt auf Kompositionsregeln, weil ich der Meinung bin, dass alles Wunderschön klingen kann. Jedes Musikstück von mir soll einzigartig sein. Ich versuche anders wie andere Hobby Komponisten zu sein und mache bewusst Musik die auch sehr gewöhnungsbedürftig ist. The reasons for my interests come from my general enthusiasm for learning and reading about everything. I chose science because that seemed to be my strength, which derived from my curiosity in nature. As I grew up, my interests evolved around subjects in school, particularly in biology, chemistry and physics in high school. These interests were furthered in time spent in the deserts and forests of Arizona, where we moved when I was in my teens. The desert was not totally new to me, having visited relatives in Phoenix several times before moving there, however, out exploring the desert on my own was new.
